article.headline: Rice 64, East Carolina 47
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Morris Almond had a double-double with a team-best 18 points and 10 rebounds to lead Rice past East Carolina 64-47 on Saturday. Almond made five 3-pointers for Rice (8-7, 2-0 Conference USA), which led by as many as 25. Lorenzo Williams scored 17 points and Patrick Britton finished with 10. Courtney Captain scored 18 points to lead the Pirates (5-10, 0-2), and freshman John Fields grabbed 13 rebounds. Greg Killings scored on a lay-up to start a 10-0 spurt that snapped a 10-10 tie and gave the Owls a 20-10 lead midway through the first half. Rice pushed the lead to 16 and made it 32-16 at the break. Chris Hagan scored on a lay-up to extend the lead to 21, 39-18, early in the second half. Captain hit a pair of 3-pointers and Darrell Jenkins added one of his own on the Pirates next three possessions to cut the Rice lead to 14, 41-27, with 15:49 remaining. Rice extended its lead to 25, 64-39, with an 18-7 run to help secure the win.
